The paper deals with human pose estimation using RGB-D data, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The proposed method also involves learning with a combination of RGB-only and RGB-D datasets, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of a depth ranking learning objective and a constraint generator module suggests the involvement of robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) subfields.
